text: Phryneta semirasa is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Dohrn in 1885. It is known from Tanzania, the Democratic Republic of the Congo, Mozambique, Zimbabwe, Malawi, and Zambia.BioLib.cz - Phryneta semirasa.
